{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5d4f5732-c349-4df2-8afd-3196522dfd5d","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped VSTest support by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **3.8**, the default test runner changed from VSTest to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP)**. In **4.x**, the VSTest compatibility layer is no longer included at all, so `vstest.console` can't discover or run your tests.\n\n### Your options\n\n1. **Switch your CI to use `dotnet test`** (recommended) — MTP is invoked automatically:\n   ```\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n\n2. **If you must keep `vstest.console`**, re-enable the VSTest bridge by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nOption 1 is the recommended path forward since MTP is the intended runner for MSTest.Sdk 4.x.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d3ff68f5-0466-4174-abe1-8c531e70d736","outputTokens":249,"requestId":"A03E:356307:1CE26A3:21106C1:69FEA4CC"},"id":"09bfd258-dde1-4d35-a432-ab9b091f579d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T03:06:58.510Z","parentId":"cc7d1e64-bf34-4ab0-aea2-39ef7cfe00ce"}
